edu.uci.calismall
Class CaliSmallElement

java.lang.Object
  edu.uci.calismall.CaliSmallElement
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparable<CaliSmallElement>
Direct Known Subclasses:
Scrap
public abstract class CaliSmallElement
extends Object
implements Comparable<CaliSmallElement>

A graphical item used in CaliSmall.

CaliSmallElement's all take some space in the main Canvas; to speed up intersection/inclusion tests a (PointF,float, float) triplet is kept for every CaliSmallElement: the first element represents the coordinates of the top-left corner of the RectF enclosing the element the two floats are the rectangle width and height. This way a binary search can be performed to filter potential candidates (a more refined test is to be performed afterwards using Region's).

Every CaliSmallElement CaliSmallElement's need not be primitive, i.e. a CaliSmallElement may contain another one (as for Stroke's within Scrap's).

Author:
Michele Bonazza
